Sonia Gandhi: Sonia Gandhi abroad for check-up, may miss poll results 
9-3-2017 
Times News NetworkNew Delhi: Congress chief Sonia Gandhi has flown abroad for a medical check-up and is likely to be away during the criti- cal week ahead when results of the five state polls will be announced. Sonia left on Wednesday night and sources said she is likely to be back on March 21-22.The Congress chief has been routinely going out for medical checkup since she underwent treatment for an undisclosed ailment in 2011.Later, she fell ill during a roadshow in Varanasi in August 2016 and had to return midway through her campaign. In the following months, her son and party vice-president Rahul Gandhi has chaired key party meetings like CWC and a national convention in the capital. Rahul also spearheaded the party campaign in the five state polls while Sonia stayed away. 
